  <h2>Key Features</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Controller-Agent separation</strong> вҖ” state lives exclusively in the Controller; agents are stateless workers that pull work via gRPC streaming RPCs.</li>
    <li><strong>mTLS authentication</strong> вҖ” all gRPC traffic is encrypted and mutually authenticated using per-agent certificates issued by the Controller's built-in CA.</li>
    <li><strong>Priority FIFO scheduling</strong> вҖ” jobs carry an integer priority; within the same priority the queue is first-in, first-out. The scheduler matches jobs to capable agents based on codec requirements and GPU availability.</li>
    <li><strong>Adaptive chunked encoding</strong> вҖ” the Controller splits long sources into segments and distributes chunks across multiple agents in parallel, then concatenates the output.</li>
    <li><strong>Offline resilience</strong> вҖ” agents maintain a local SQLite journal; they can survive a Controller outage and resume reporting when connectivity is restored.</li>
    <li><strong>Template-driven script generation</strong> вҖ” AviSynth and VapourSynth filter scripts are generated from Jinja-style templates, allowing custom filter chains per preset.</li>
    <li><strong>Real-time WebSocket events</strong> вҖ” all job state transitions, agent heartbeats, and log lines are broadcast over WebSocket so the React dashboard updates without polling.</li>
    <li><strong>Plugin-based codec system</strong> вҖ” encoding backends are Go interface implementations registered at startup, making it straightforward to add new codecs.</li>
    <li><strong>Prometheus metrics</strong> вҖ” the Controller and each Agent expose <code>/metrics</code> endpoints compatible with Prometheus scraping and the included Grafana dashboards.</li>
  </ul>

